Bringing all the flavours of festive roast veggies to a delicious pastry, this Caramelised Root Veg and Onion Tart with Flaked Almonds and Balsamic Dressed Salad is a warming, delicious meal for the season ahead.

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @puff pastry sheet{1} from your fridge.

Trim the @carrot{2} and @parsnip{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons and pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle the veg with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once roasted, drizzle the @red pepper chilli jelly{25%g} over the veg and toss to coat.

While the veg roasts, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, unroll the pastry (keeping it on its baking paper) and lay it onto a baking tray.

Using a #knife{}, score a 2cm border all around - be careful not to cut all the way through. Prick the pastry all over with a #fork{}, keeping inside the border.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until it starts to colour and puff up, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In the meantime, combine the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the pastry has baked, remove it from the oven and push down the centre with the back of a #spoon{}.

Gently spread the creamy sauce over the base of the tart, then an even layer of caramelised onion. Top with the roasted carrots and parsnips, then scatter over the @toasted flaked almonds{25%g}.

Return the tart to the top shelf of your oven to bake until golden brown, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, clean the (now empty) #sauce bowl{}. Add the @olive oil{for the dressing}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the dressing and toss to coat.

When ready, slice the tart and share between your plates.

Serve the salad alongside and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!